<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(255, 47, 146); font-size: 18px;">Docker Client Installation</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">=&gt; cd /usr/ports/sysutils/docker</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">=&gt; sudo make install clean</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"># Conflicts with the server installation</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"># Looks like the Docker Server installs the Client too.</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 18px;">Server Installation</span></div><div># You need to install this package:</div><div># To enables SSL Certificate Verification</div><div>=&gt; sudo pkg install -y ca_root_nss</div><div><br /></div><div># Before installing the Docker you need to setup</div><div># the dataset for it.</div><div>=&gt; sudo zfs create zroot/usr/docker</div><div># Mount it to “/usr/docker”</div><div>=&gt; sudo zfs set  mountpoint=/usr/docker zroot/usr/docker</div><div><br /></div><div># Note: You could have done above two commands with</div><div># this single line:</div><div># =&gt; sudo zfs create -o mountpoint=/usr/docker zroot/docker</div><div><br /></div><div># Installing the Docker server</div><div>=&gt; cd /usr/ports/sysutils/docker-freebsd</div><div>=&gt; sudo make install clean</div><div><br /></div><div># Enable the Docker service in the “/etc/rc.conf"</div><div>=&gt; sudo sysrc -f /etc/rc.conf docker_enable="YES"</div><div>=&gt; sudo service docker start</div></en-note>